{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4784f343-ca71-4592-8b8d-d0372b83ad61","content":"There's no pipeline file in the repo, so here's general guidance for the migration:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console.exe`, so `VSTest@3` won't work. Use a script step instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=testresults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **TRX reports** — The `--logger trx` flag still works with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Publish them with:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n   ```\n\n2. **Code coverage** — Use `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"` and publish:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n\n3. **Project changes** — Ensure your test `.csproj` files enable the new platform:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Package** — Update to `MSTest` 3.x+ (or `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` ≥ 3.x) which includes `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`.\n\nThe critical difference: `VSTest@3` invokes `vstest.console.exe` which is incompatible with `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`. You must switch to `dotnet test` (or run the test executable directly).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e9248231-c75b-4a74-9d35-44134b7e1931","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the directory. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":601,"requestId":"4813:136CC7:2FC3FB1:345BB8E:69FBE2A8"},"id":"f8c0c45f-2ca7-478b-95bd-fd771886a7af","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:11.695Z","parentId":"273ba65b-02c8-43b5-a994-6293128d8e2d"}
